    "comment": "Rationale: Dvl1 was detected in Liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry results of LDCVs.\nFigure 3B: Post-embedding immunogold (inset) staining against Dvl1 displays localisation on the surface of LDCV.\nFigure 4: Dvl1-myc was transfected in PC12 cells, immunostaining demonstrates Dvl1 localisation on vesicular structures indicating that Dvl1 is a vesicular protein.\nFigure 3A and S2D: Fzd8 immunoreaction was present on LDCVs and did not colocalise with SP or CGRP (DCV markers) indicating that LDCVs might have another subset that does not have SP or CGRP.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper does not provide any information on the specificity of the antibody used.. Experimental description: No mention of mouse strain used ...Authors were contacted for retrieving this information (15/05/2020 Dnyanada, xu.zhang@ion.ac.cn)",
